rudedatabase
------------------------------------------
The RudeDatabase? Open Source C++ database library makes programming with
MySQL databases fast and simple. It has all the functionality, but removes the
headaches involved with learning the mySql API. Requires one header file, one
RudeServer library file, and the mySqlClient library file for your platform.
The Singleton architecture of the Database library provides simplicity and
efficiency for Model-View-Controller type architectures.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.7-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libmysqlclient16-5.1.47-1
  libstdc++6-4.3.4-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-9-1
  automake-4-10
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.10.2-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.rudeserver.com/database/

Canonical download:
  http://www.rudeserver.com/database/download/rudedatabase-4.1.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack rudedatabase-4.1.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./rudedatabase-4.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rudedatabase-4.1.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/rudedatabase-4.1.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/librudedatabase4-4.1.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/librudedatabase-devel-4.1.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

